a) Do While Loop (Print numbers from 5 to 1)

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio and create a New Process
Step 2: Open Main.xaml
Step 3: Drag a Sequence into the workspace (if not already present)
Step 4: Create a variable:
Name: num
Type: Int32
Default Value: 5

Step 5: Drag a Do While activity inside the Sequence
Step 6: Set the condition of Do While: num >= 1
Step 7: Inside the Do While body, drag a Write Line activity
Step 8: Set its value:
num.ToString
Step 9: Drag an Assign activity below Write Line
Step 10: Set:
num = num - 1
Step 11: Run the workflow

b) Delay Activity (5 seconds gap)

Step 1: Open Main.xaml
Step 2: Drag a Sequence

Step 3: Drag a Write Line activity
Step 4: Enter:

"First message"

Step 5: Drag a Delay activity below it
Step 6: Set Duration:

00:00:05

Step 7: Drag another Write Line activity
Step 8: Enter:

"Second message"

Step 9: Run the workflow

 c) If Condition (Decision Making)

Step 1: Open Main.xaml
Step 2: Drag a Sequence
Step 3: Create a variable:
Name: num
Type: Int32
Value: 10

Step 4: Drag an If activity
Step 5: Set the condition:

num Mod 2 = 0

Step 6: In the Then section, add a Write Line
Step 7: Enter:
"Number is Even"

Step 8: In the Else section, add a Write Line
Step 9: Enter:
"Number is Odd"

Step 10: Run the workflow
